---
// Campaign loop: build environment → red-teaming → findings → back into build.
---

<figure
  class="loop-diagram"
  aria-label="Campaign loop: build environment, red-team, findings, fed back into the build"
>
  <div class="loop-svg-wrap">
    <svg
      viewBox="0 0 720 400"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <defs>
        <marker
          id="loop-arrow"
          viewBox="0 0 10 10"
          refX="9"
          refY="5"
          markerWidth="9"
          markerHeight="9"
          orient="auto"
        >
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="#a00"></path>
        </marker>
      </defs>
      <g fill="none" stroke="#a00" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round">
        <path d="M 460 90 Q 680 175 580 270" marker-end="url(#loop-arrow)"></path>
        <path d="M 470 345 Q 360 395 250 345" marker-end="url(#loop-arrow)"></path>
        <path d="M 140 270 Q 40 175 260 90" marker-end="url(#loop-arrow)"></path>
      </g>
    </svg>

    <div class="loop-label" style="top: 17.5%; left: 50%;">
      <span class="t">Build Environment</span>
      <span class="s">custom infrastructure and agent harnesses</span>
    </div>

    <div class="loop-label" style="top: 78%; left: 78%;">
      <span class="t">Red-Teaming</span>
      <span class="s">Stress-test the agents under heat</span>
    </div>

    <div class="loop-label" style="top: 78%; left: 22%;">
      <span class="t">Findings</span>
      <span class="s">surfaced, reported on, and fed back into the build</span>
    </div>

    <div class="loop-center">Iterative feedback loop</div>
  </div>
  <figcaption>
    outputs:<strong>&nbsp;safety reports</strong> · <strong
      >testing infrastructure · agent runtimes</strong
    >
  </figcaption>
</figure>
